observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Treasurer 
(a) follow the set deadline for the submission of documents to the Municipal Accountant before the year-end for all unsettled/unpaid lawful expenditures and obligations for the recording in the books;
(b) forward all the disbursement vouchers together with their supporting documents for all the checks issued to the Municipal Accountant; 
(c) ensure that all the checks prepared during the year are released accordingly and the pertinent documents forwarded to the Municipal Accountant; and 
(d) forward the documents to the Municipal Accountant for all unreleased checks for the recording of the payable account.

We recommended that the (a) MDRRMO prepare 

(i) a comprehensive and an in-depth LDRRMP by presenting as functional classification the four thematic areas of disaster risk reduction and management such as disaster prevention and mitigation, disaster preparedness, disaster response, and disaster rehabilitation and recovery;


(ii) the required PPMP for consolidation in the APP; 


(b) Municipal Budget Officer see to it that all charges in the LDRRMF are calamity-related expenses; 


(c) Municipal Accountant consistently follow the accounting guidelines on the recording of purchases to the appropriate inventory account and, together with the Requisitioning Officer, install an effective internal control in the recording of receipts and issuances by maintaining the supplies ledger cards and stock cards, respectively.

We recommended that the 

(a) LDRRM Officer include in the LDRRMFIP the projects and activities to be funded from the unexpended LDRRMF of previous years and prepare the required PPMP for consolidation in the APP; 

(b) Municipal Budget Officer see to it that all charges in the LDRRMF are within the approved budget; 



(c) Municipal Accountant follow the accounting guidelines on the recording of purchases to the appropriate inventory account and together with the Requisitioning Officer, install an effective internal control in the recording of receipts and issuances by maintaining the supplies ledger cards and stock cards, respectively; and 

(d) Requisitioning Office submit the list of recipients indicating the number of sacks issued for proper accounting thereof.

We recommended that the 

(a) Management 

(i) allow only the payment of meals and snacks expenses for specific programs and/or activities or in the conduct of official business, reception or entertainment as contemplated in the law; 



(ii) refrain from allowing meals and snacks expenses of officials and employees with fixed representation allowance incurred in their travels and/or performance of their regular duties; 

(b) Members of the BAC and Secretariat see to it that the procurement process is observed; 



(c) Municipal Budget Officer see to it that all charges are within the approved budget; and 



(d) Municipal Accountant properly review the completeness of documentary requirements to substantiate the propriety and legality of the transactions.

1.11     We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:
require the Inventory Committee  to conduct a complete physical inventory of PPE to determine the actual existence of all assets owned by the Municipality;
direct the Property Officer (i) to submit a properly and completely accomplished physical inventory report duly reconciled with the accounting records; and (ii) to assign property number/tag for each PPE;
require the Property Officer and the Municipal Accountant (i) to reconcile the property and the accounting records of the PPE accounts balances with the physical inventory report; and (ii) to have a complete maintenance and keeping of updated PCs, and PPELCs and RPLCs for each category of assets to facilitate the reconciliation process between these offices; and
require the Municipal Treasurer to ascertain the status of parcels of land owned by the Municipality with titling issues and work for the titling thereof in the name of the Municipality of Santa Rita, assuming funds have been provided therefore.

2.21	We recommended that the:
Members of the MDRRMC (i) update the Comprehensive Municipal Disaster Risk Reduction Management (MDRRM) and Climate Change Adaptation (CCA) Plan pursuant to DILG Memorandum Circular 2015-77;
MDRRMO  (i) prepare a comprehensive and an in-depth LDRRMP encompassing the four (4) thematic areas of disaster risk reduction and management such as disaster prevention and mitigation, disaster preparedness, disaster response, and disaster rehabilitation and recovery in alignment with the recommended activities contained in the Comprehensive Municipal Disaster Risk Reduction Management (MDRRM) and Climate Change Adaptation (CCA) Plan; (ii) submit the LDRRMP to the Local Sanggunian for approval through the Local DRRM Council for their review; and (iii) organize and conduct training, orientation and knowledge management activities on disaster risk reduction and management at the local level on a continuing basis to maintain, provide or arrange the provision of or to otherwise make available, suitably-trained and competent personnel for effective civil defense and disaster risk reduction and management in its area;
Municipal Budget Officer see to it that all charges in the LDRRMF are calamity/disaster related expenses and in consonance with the approved programs/activities in the LDRRMP; and
Municipal Accountant together with the Municipal Treasurer (i) facilitate the transfer of unexpended balance of the LDRMF to the Trust Fund accounts of ₱1,396,625.05; and (ii) install an effective internal control in the recording, maintenance and distribution of relief items and other disaster supplies in accordance with the above-mentioned rules and regulations.

3.16	We recommended that the:
Members of the Municipal Local School Board allocate the SEF budget only for eligible and priority program, projects and activities allowed by the law and encourage schools to make use of the DepEd’s funds for their regular operations;
Members of the Municipal Local School Board and Municipal Budget Officer ensure that all charges in the SEF are within the adherence to the provisions of R.A. 5447, Section 100 and 272, RA 7160 and DepEd-DBM-DILG Joint Circular No. 01, s. 2017 dated January 19, 2017 in the preparation of the CY 2018 SEF budget and in the utilization of the CY 2017 Local School Board Fund;
Members of the Municipal Local School Board thru the Municipal Accountant and Treasurer, allow only the grant of cash advances for time-bound activities to duly designated disbursing officers who are bonded; and
Members of the Municipal Local School Board submit above-cited lacking documents and henceforth, ensure that all claims are supported by proper reports and comply with the required documentation for similar transactions.
